{"body": [{"indent": 0, "text": ["Volume Rasterize Curve"], "type": "title", "extent": [121, 148], "level": 0}, {"indent": 0, "type": "summary", "extent": [148, 188], "text": ["Converts a curve into a volume."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [188, 657], "text": ["The Volume Rasterize operation takes a curve and creates a VDB volume based on it. It has been designed to complement ", {"text": ["Draw Curve SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/drawcurve", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/drawcurve"}, " since it will use point attributes created by the ", {"text": ["Stroke SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/stroke", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/stroke"}, " such as ", {"text": ["stroke_pressure"], "type": "code"}, ", but will work with a standard curve created using a ", {"text": ["Draw Curve"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/drawcurve", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/drawcurve"}, ". It will create the needed attributes with default values of 1. The volumes created are based on the ", {"text": ["Output"], "type": "ui"}, " parameters."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [657, 946], "text": ["The point attributes ", {"text": ["pscale"], "type": "code"}, " and ", {"text": ["density"], "type": "code"}, " are used to control the generated volume. They are derived from ", {"text": ["width"], "type": "code"}, " and ", {"text": ["stroke_pressure"], "type": "code"}, " that are created by the ", {"text": ["Draw Curve"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/drawcurve", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/drawcurve"}, "/", {"text": ["Stroke"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/stroke", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/stroke"}, " SOPs. If missing, it will create those values at default value of 1."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [946, 1127], "text": ["This asset is used as a building block in ", {"text": ["Paint Color Volume"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/paintcolorvolume", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/paintcolorvolume"}, ",\n", {"text": ["Paint Mask Volume"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/paintmaskvolume", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/paintmaskvolume"}, ", ", {"text": ["Paint SDF Volume"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/paintsdfvolume", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/paintsdfvolume"}, "."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [1133, 1223], "text": ["If missing stroke point attributes this asset will create default ones set to 1."]}], "indent": 0, "role": "item", "type": "note", "extent": [1127, 1133]}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "note_group"}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [1247, 1433], "text": ["Type of volume created. ", {"text": ["Color"], "type": "ui"}, " creates a float density field and a vector 3 ", {"text": ["Cd"], "type": "code"}, " field. ", {"text": ["Mask"], "type": "ui"}, " creates a float density field. ", {"text": ["SDF"], "type": "ui"}, " creates a float signed surface field."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Output"], "role": "item", "extent": [1235, 1247], "type": "parameters_item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "parameters_item_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 1, "text": "Parameters", "role": "section", "extent": [1223, 1235], "container": true, "type": "parameters_section", "id": "parameters"}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [1462, 1514], "text": ["Size of the voxels of the created volume"]}], "indent": 4, "type": "dt", "extent": [1446, 1462], "text": ["Voxel Size"]}], "container": true, "type": "dt_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 2, "text": ["Volume"], "extent": [1433, 1446], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": null}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [1561, 1740], "text": ["Multiple volumes are merged together with their densities unaffected. When off the volumes are combined according to their density which is treated like an alpha channel."]}], "indent": 4, "type": "dt", "extent": [1526, 1561], "text": ["Fast Composite (Color Output)"]}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [1774, 1977], "text": ["When on the setup uses ", {"text": ["Volume Rasterize Particles"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/volumerasterizeparticles", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/volumerasterizeparticles"}, " which has minimal controls but is much faster than ", {"text": ["Volume Rasterize Points"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/volumerasterizepoints", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/volumerasterizepoints"}, "."]}], "indent": 4, "type": "dt", "extent": [1740, 1774], "text": ["Fast Rasterize (Mask Output)"]}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [1996, 2030], "text": ["Density field multiplier."]}], "indent": 4, "type": "dt", "extent": [1977, 1996], "text": ["Density Scale"]}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [2047, 2091], "text": ["Distance used to sample the curves."]}], "indent": 4, "type": "dt", "extent": [2030, 2047], "text": ["Sample Rate"]}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [2101, 2169], "text": ["Falloff of the density over the length of the stroke curve."]}], "indent": 4, "type": "dt", "extent": [2091, 2101], "text": ["Fade"]}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [2184, 2261], "text": ["Strength of the density created over the length of the stroke curve."]}], "indent": 4, "type": "dt", "extent": [2169, 2184], "text": ["Flow Rate"]}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [2292, 2376], "text": ["Specifies which operation is used when merging multiple curves densities."]}], "indent": 3, "type": "dt", "extent": [2261, 2292], "text": ["Merge Method (Mask Output)"]}], "container": true, "type": "dt_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 2, "text": ["Brush"], "extent": [1514, 1526], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": null}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "b